{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ζώννῡμι</b> <br /> (ὑπο-ζωνύναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.73.9), (παρα-) 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 553c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>ζωννύω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “γυναικεῖα” 1.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i> ἐζώννυον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.John.21.18 \">NT</a>]: <i>future</i> ζώσω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.29.9, NT.John.21.18\">LXX+NT</a>]: <i>aorist 1</i> ἔζωσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.76, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 14 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἔζωκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 8.40.2, (δι-) 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 2.5 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i> (see. below [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11)\">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist 1</i> ἐζώσθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" (δι-) 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Signis Tempestatum” 22: \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> ἔζωμαι (δι-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.6 cited in 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc., 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus see at {σέσωται}, _3rd.pers._ _sing._ ἔζωται (δι-) “IG” 22.1491.36, (ὑπ-) [prev. work]1621.68, ἔζωσται 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Art.” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>][same place]; also in <i>middle</i> sense (see. below): rare in <i>Attic dialect</i>, even in compounds:—<b>gird</b>, especially <b>gird round the loins</b> for a pugilistic conflict (see. below), ἄγον ζώσαντες ἀνάγκῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.76 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] (here only <i>active</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus); ζῶσέ [μιν].. Ἀθήνη 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 72 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ζ. τινά <b>hug</b> him in wrestling, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 8.40.2 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ζ. γαῖαν, of Ocean, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 9.778 (1st c.AD: Philippus Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ζ. νῆα ὅπλῳ,= ὑποζώννυμι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11, 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 1.368: with double _accusative_, ζ. τινὰ ζώνην LXX.Lev.8.7, cf. LXX.1Ki.17.39. \">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>ζώννῠμαι</b>, <b>gird oneself</b>, especially of athletes. γυμνός, ζωννυμένων τῶν πρὶν ἐνὶ σταδίῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.52.6 (Megara, 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὼ δὲ ζωσαμένω βήτην ἐς μέσσον ἀγῶνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.685, compare 710; ζώννυνταί τε νέοι καὶ ἐπεντύνονται ἄεθλα 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.89; Ὀδυσσεὺς ζώσατο μὲν ῥάκεσιν περὶ μήδεα 18.67, compare 1st c.BC: Parthenius Mythographus 10.2. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>gird up one's loins</b> for battle, ζώννυσθαι ἄνωγεν Ἀργείους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.15; ζώννυσθαι [ζωστῆρι] 10.78 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i>, ὅθι ζωννύσκετο μίτρην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5.857 (vulgar form); ζώσατο δὲ ζώνην 14.181 (vulgar form); χαλκὸν ζώννυσθαι 23.130; ἐς γόνυ μέχρι χιτῶνα ζώννυσθαι 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Dianam” 12; χιτῶνα εἰς μηρὸν ἔζωστο 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 4; for labour, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 345; ἐπὶ βουσίν 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 1.426, etc.; ζώννυσθαι τὰς κοιλίας ζώναις 4th c.BC: Theopompus Historicus 39a. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be fixed by means of girths</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.6.37. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>to be formed in belts</b> or <b>seams</b>, καδμεία ἐζωσμένη (ἐξωσμ- codices) probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pseudo-Democritus Alchemista Alch. p.45B. (compare ζωνῖτις). (ζω(ς)- from I.- 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>yōs-</b>, cf. Lithuanian <i>júosti</i> 'to gird', <b>júostas</b>, Avest. <b>yāsta-</b>,= ζωστός 'girt'.)","strongNumber":"G2224","accentedUnicode":"ζώννυμι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0328","matchingForm":"ἀναζώννυμι","stepTransliteration":"anazōnnumi","gloss":"to gird","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要束上","_es_Gloss":"ceñir","_zh_Gloss":"要束上"},{"strongNumber":"G1241","matchingForm":"διαζώννυμι","stepTransliteration":"diazōnnumi","gloss":"to tie around","_zh_tw_Gloss":"束腰","_es_Gloss":"atar","_zh_Gloss":"束腰"},{"strongNumber":"G2223","matchingForm":"ζώνη","stepTransliteration":"zōnē","gloss":"belt/sash/girdle","_zh_tw_Gloss":"帶","_es_Gloss":"cinturón/faja","_zh_Gloss":"带"},{"strongNumber":"G4024","matchingForm":"περιζώννυμι","stepTransliteration":"perizōnnumi","gloss":"to gird","_zh_tw_Gloss":"束著","_es_Gloss":"ceñir","_zh_Gloss":"束着"},{"strongNumber":"G5269","matchingForm":"ὑποζώννυμι","stepTransliteration":"hupozōnnumi","gloss":"to undergird","_zh_tw_Gloss":"捆綁","_es_Gloss":"reforzar","_zh_Gloss":"捆绑"}],"shortDef":"to dress, clothe oneself, put on a belt or sash","mediumDef":"to dress, clothe oneself, put on a belt or sash","stepGloss":"to dress","stepTransliteration":"zōnnumi","count":3,"_es_Definition":"ceñirse, ceñirse el cinturón ; vestirse","_zh_tw_Definition":"束上 (約 21:18)","_zh_Definition":"束上 (约 21:18)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"thắt lưng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"束上","_es_Gloss":"vestir","_zh_Gloss":"束上"}]}